## 4 · Front‑End Guidelines
4.1 **Styling Consistency** Match the existing design system; avoid unnecessary visual changes.  
4.2 **Responsive by Default** Use fluid layouts & dynamic units.  
4.3 **Modularity** Extract reusable hooks/components; separate presentation, state, and API logic.  
4.4 **UX Principles** Fast loads, optimistic updates, clear async feedback.  

---

## 5 · Git & Change Management
5.1 **Atomic Commits** Group related edits; unrelated fixes get separate commits.  
5.2 **Commit Message Format** `<scope>: <imperative message> (ISSUE‑123)`; add a short body if helpful.  
5.3 **Rollback Safety** Avoid irreversible migrations unless approved; supply down‑migrations when applicable.  

---

## 6 · Critical Notes
6.1 **No Hard‑Coded Secrets or Stub Data** Wire to real configs/APIs or ask me.  
6.2 **Implement Only What I Ask** Before adding features, verify they don’t already exist.  
6.3 **Seek Simplicity** Favor the simplest complete solution; avoid over‑engineering.  
6.4 **When Unsure, Ask** Request clarification *before* proceeding if anything is missing or unclear.  

